snippet.title: We Build Black Hole Making Machine -100% Real | Part-1
snippet.description:
Please Watch Part-2 Also. Everything You Will See In Part2 Is Real. NO Vfx or Graphics Are Used. Our Machine Will Create Something Which Looks Like Black Hole, Galaxy, Supernova, Universe etc.

A black hole is a region of spacetime where gravity is so strong that nothing, including light or other electromagnetic waves has enough energy to escape its event horizon. 

Our blackhole have also powerful gravity in the center and can pull a human size object inside the center.

#blackhole #mrindianhacker #science

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Song: Aye Watan Tere Liye
Movie: Karma
Singer: Mohammad Aziz, Kavita Krishnamurthy

Music: Laxmikant Pyarelal

Mera karma tu mera dharma tu 
tera sab kuch mai mera sab kuch tu
[har karam apna karenge
har karam apna karenge aye watan tere liye
dil diya hai jan bhi denge aye watan tere liye] (x2)

tu mera karma tu mera dharma tu mera abhimaan hai
aye watan mehbub mere tujhpe dil kurbaan hai
aye watan mehbub mere tujhpe dil kurban hai
hum jiyenge or marenge aye watan tere liye
dil diya hai jaan bhi denge aye watan tere liye
dil diya hai jaan bhi denge aye watan tere liye

hindu muslim sikh isayi hum watan hum naam hai
hindu muslim sikh isayi hum watan hum naam hai
jo kare inko juda mazhab nahi ilzam hai
hum jiyenge or marenge aye watan tere liye
dil diya hai jaan bhi denge aye watan tere liye
dil diya hai jaan bhi denge aye watan tere liye

teri galiyo me chalakar nafrato ki goliya
lut te hai kuch lutere dulhano ki doliyo
lut rahe hai aap wo apne gharo ko lut kar
khelte hai bekhbar apne lahu se goliya
hum jiyenge or marenge aye watan tere liye
dil diya hai jan bhi denge aye watan tere liye

snippet.title: Tere Bin Episode 11 Teaser - 26th January 2023 - HAR PAL GEO
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Tere Bin Episode 11 Teaser - 26th January 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Writer: Nooran Makhdoom
Director: Siraj ul Haq
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi
Production House: 7th Sky Entertainment

Cast :
Yumna Zaidi as Meerab
Wahaj Ali as Murtasim
Bushra Ansari as Salma
Sohail Sameer as Anwar
Sabeena Farooq as Haya
Hira Soomro as Maryam
Fazila Qazi as Aneela
Farhan Ally Agha as Waqas
Seemi Pasha as Sabra
Mahmood Aslam as Malik Mukhtaar
Haris Waheed
Agha Mustafa

snippet.title: Republic Day 2023 |  Highlights Of The Republic Day Parade 2023 | 26th January 2023 Parade | News18
snippet.description:
Republic Day 2023 |  Highlights Of The Republic Day Parade 2023 | 26th January 2023 Parade | News18 

The 74th Republic Day Parade was about the spectacular display of made-in-India weapons, increased role of 'Nari Shakti' in the Armed Forces and signs of the country leaving behind its colonial past. For the first time in the history of India‚Äôs Republic Day, the British-era 25-pounder guns, which had been used for decades for the 21-gun salute, were replaced with the indigenous 105mm Indian Field Guns. The vintage artillery, which was once used in the World War II, fell silent and the desi guns boomed for the ceremonial gun salute. Lt Commander Disha Amrith, 29, was the first Navy woman officer to lead a naval contingent of 144 sailors, showcasing the increasing role of 'Nari Shakti' in the military. Armed with assault rifles, women soldiers in colourful uniforms, usually deployed along the desert border with Pakistan, were for the first time joined the BSF camel contingent. Women officers were also part of the contingents of Corps of Signals, Army Air Defence and Army Daredevils

SHAZAM! FURY OF THE GODS 
From New Line Cinema comes ‚ÄúShazam! Fury of the Gods,‚Äù which continues the story of teenage Billy Batson who, upon reciting the magic word ‚ÄúSHAZAM!,‚Äù is transformed into his adult Super Hero alter ego, Shazam. ‚ÄúShazam! Fury of the Gods‚Äù stars returning cast members Zachary Levi (‚ÄúThor: Ragnarok‚Äù) as Shazam; Asher Angel (‚ÄúAndi Mack‚Äù) as Billy Batson; Jack Dylan Grazer (‚ÄúIt Chapter Two‚Äù) as Freddy Freeman; Adam Brody (‚ÄúPromising Young Woman‚Äù) as Super Hero Freddy; Ross Butler (‚ÄúRaya and the Last Dragon‚Äù) as Super Hero Eugene; Meagan Good (‚ÄúDay Shift‚Äù) as Super Hero Darla; D.J. Cotrona (‚ÄúG.I. Joe: Retaliation‚Äù) as Super Hero Pedro; Grace Caroline Currey (‚ÄúAnnabelle: Creation‚Äù) as Mary Bromfield / Super Hero Mary; Faithe Herman (‚ÄúThis Is Us‚Äù) as Darla Dudley; Ian Chen (‚ÄúA Dog‚Äôs Journey‚Äù) as Eugene Choi; Jovan Armand (‚ÄúSecond Chances‚Äù) as Pedro Pena; Marta Milans (‚ÄúWhite Lines‚Äù) as Rosa Vasquez; Cooper Andrews (‚ÄúThe Walking Dead‚Äù) as Victor Vasquez; with Djimon Hounsou (‚ÄúA Quiet Place Part II‚Äù) as Wizard. Tere Bin Episode 10 - [Eng Sub] - Yumna Zaidi - Wahaj Ali - Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream - 26th January 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Tere Bin Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Writer: Nooran Makhdoom
Director: Siraj ul Haq
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi

In this video, Abhi and Niyu discuss 3 historical mistakes of Pakistan that caused Pakistan to fail and why India must learn from them. This is the 2nd episode in our Pakistan Explained.

#Pakistan #Economy #abhiandniyu 

What is Pakistan Economic Crisis?

 Pakistan‚Äôs financial crisis is worsening and the country‚Äôs economy could soon hit rock bottom. In just a matter of three weeks, the South Asian nation‚Äôs inflation has skyrocketed to levels never seen before, and severe food and energy shortages have left over 200 million citizens in huge distress.

A couple of days ago, the world got another glimpse of Pakistan‚Äôs acute financial crisis, as the nation plunged into darkness following its worst power outage in months. The country‚Äôs overburdened electrical system collapsed on January 23, leading to a nationwide blackout that even impacted densely populated cities like Karachi, Islamabad, Lahore and Peshawar.

Are you curious about the current economic crisis in Pakistan? Look no further! Our video provides a thorough analysis of the current economic crisis in Pakistan, discussing the root causes, the impact on the population, and potential solutions. From inflation and unemployment to the devaluation of the rupee and the country's debt crisis, our experts break down the complex issues in a way that is easy to understand. With interviews from leading economists and government officials, you'll get a well-rounded understanding of the current situation. Don't miss this in-depth look at the Pakistan economic crisis. Make sure to like and share the video, and subscribe to our channel for more informative content on current events and global issues.

üî∏ Lyrics of Bharat Ka Rehnewaala Hoon :

jab zero diya mere bharat ne

yu chand pe jana mushkil tha

sabhyta jaha pahle aayi

hai prit jaha ki rit sada, hai prit jaha ki rit sada

bharat ka rahne wala hu, bharat kie baat sunata hu
hai prit jaha ki rit sada

kale gore ka bhed nahi, har dil se hamara nata hai
kuch aur na aata ho hamko, hame pyar nibhana aata hai
jise maan chuki sari duniya, ho jise maan chuki sari duniya
main baat, main baat wahi dohrata hu
bharat ka rahne wala hu, bharat kie baat sunata hu
hai prit jaha ki rit sada

jaha ram abhi tak hai nar me, nari me abhi tak sita hai
itne pawan hai log jaha, ho itne pawan hai log jaha
mai nit nit, mai nit nit shish jhukata hu
bharat ka rahne wala hu, bharat kie baat sunata hu

itni mamta nadiyo ko bhi, jaha maata kah ke bulate hai
itna aadar insan to kya, patthar bhi puje jate hai
us dharti pe maine janam liya
ho us dharti pe maine janam liya, ye soch
ye soch ke mai itraata hoo
bharat kaa rahane waala hoo, bharat ki baat sunaata hoo
hai prit jaha ki rit sada

About Film Companion South:
Film Companion South is a division of Film Companion, founded by film critic and author Anupama Chopra. Apart from film reviews and articles, Film Companion South, with programs in Tamil, Malayalam, Telugu, and Kannada, specializes in conducting in-depth interviews with film personalities which include the likes of Kamal Hassan, Mani Ratnam, Academy Award-winner AR Rahman, Vetrimaaran, Dhanush, Yash, Sruthi Hariharan, Mahesh Babu, NTR Jr, Samantha, Aishwarya Rajesh, Ramya Krishnan, Prithviraj, Anjali Menon, Mysskin, Gautam Vasudev Menon, Rajamouli, Ram Charan, Yash, Prashanth Neel, Venkat Prabhu, Nelson, Sivakarthikeyan, Rakshit Shetty and many more. The channel has also hosted shows which open up the lesser-known facets of filmmaking with conversations with PC Sreeram, Ravi Varman, Rajiv Menon, Thota Tharani, and Academy Award-winner Resul Pookutty. In other words, Film Companion South is for those who love their cinema and are unapologetic about it.

#tamiltrekker #mongolia #coldest 

Hey backpackers, get ready for my exciting Mongolia series. Here's my vlog for the first day, sharing my day-1 experience with -27 degrees Celsius. 

My new year's first international trip started in Mongolia, and you can't imagine the freezing weather that welcomed me! If you're looking for a pleasant season to visit Mongolia, I recommend visiting when it's less cold. 

Watch my latest travel vlog to learn about Mongolia's relationship with India, local travelling, and more.
